To implement the WebRTC component, you can use the WebRTC API provided by the browser. The API provides a set of functions and events that can be used to establish a peer-to-peer connection between two browsers.

The WebRTC component should have the following functionalities:

1. Establishing a peer-to-peer connection between two browsers.
2. Sending and receiving data over the connection.
3. Handling errors and disconnections.

To communicate with the Game Board Component, the WebRTC component should have a well-defined interface. The interface should include functions for sending and receiving data related to the game.

